    <h1 class="heading1">Gynecology Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our Gynecology Department is dedicated to providing comprehensive and compassionate care for women's health needs. Led by a team of experienced gynecologists, obstetricians, and women's health specialists, we offer a range of services to address gynecological concerns, promote reproductive health, and support women through every stage of life.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Well-Woman Exams</h4>
            <p>We offer routine well-woman exams to assess overall health, screen for gynecological conditions, and provide preventive care. Our gynecologists perform pelvic exams, Pap smears, breast exams, and other screenings to detect early signs of cervical cancer, breast cancer, sexually transmitted infections (STIs), and other gynecological issues.</p>

            <h4>Family Planning and Contraception</h4>
            <p>We provide comprehensive family planning services and contraception counseling to help women make informed choices about birth control options. Our gynecologists offer contraceptive implants, intrauterine devices (IUDs), birth control pills, patches, injections, and barrier methods, tailoring recommendations to each woman's preferences, lifestyle, and reproductive goals.</p>

            <h4>Management of Menstrual Disorders</h4>
            <p>For women experiencing irregular periods, heavy bleeding, painful periods, or other menstrual disorders, our Gynecology Department offers diagnostic evaluations and personalized treatment plans. Our gynecologists provide medical management, hormonal therapies, minimally invasive procedures, and surgical interventions to address menstrual irregularities and improve quality of life.</p>

            <h4>Menopause Management</h4>
            <p>We offer comprehensive menopause management services to help women navigate the hormonal changes and symptoms associated with menopause. Our gynecologists provide hormone replacement therapy (HRT), non-hormonal therapies, lifestyle counseling, and support to manage hot flashes, night sweats, mood changes, vaginal dryness, and other menopausal symptoms.</p>

            <h4>Gynecological Surgery</h4>
            <p>Our Gynecology Department specializes in a wide range of gynecological surgeries to treat conditions such as fibroids, ovarian cysts, endometriosis, pelvic organ prolapse, and gynecological cancers. Our gynecologists perform minimally invasive laparoscopic surgery, robotic-assisted surgery, hysteroscopic procedures, and traditional open surgery, utilizing advanced techniques to minimize pain, scarring, and recovery time.</p>

            <h4>Maternity Care and Obstetrics</h4>
            <p>For expectant mothers, we provide comprehensive maternity care and obstetric services to support a healthy pregnancy and childbirth experience. Our obstetricians offer prenatal care, prenatal screenings, childbirth education, labor and delivery services, postpartum care, and breastfeeding support, ensuring the best possible outcomes for both mother and baby.</p>
        </div>
